# MCP-Aware Workflow

If the Cursor environment has MCP tools configured, use them when available.

## Qase MCP

Use Qase MCP to:

1. Parse the project code and suite ID from Qase URL.
2. Fetch all cases in the suite.
3. Fetch full details for each case.
4. Update corrected cases.
5. Create missing cases when needed.
6. Report created and updated case IDs.

Qase suite URL format:

```text
https://app.qase.io/project/{PROJECT}/suite/{SUITE_ID}
```

If only suite ID is provided, use the configured default project such as `QASE_PROJECT`.

## Jira MCP

Use Jira MCP to fetch:

- summary
- description
- acceptance criteria
- definition of done
- comments with clarified requirements
- linked defects
- linked implementation tickets

## Playwright MCP

Use Playwright MCP for app or staging URLs when available.

Build a UI inventory by checking:

- visible fields
- required indicators
- placeholders
- buttons
- tabs
- modals
- dropdowns
- validation messages
- navigation flows
- default states
- disabled states
- empty states
- confirmation dialogs
- responsive behavior when relevant

Take screenshots for important states if supported.

If MCP tools are not available, produce a review report and recommended updates that a QA engineer can apply manually.

