# Critical Rules

Do not skip any field.

Do not leave Type different from Regression.

Do not leave Layer different from E2E.

Do not leave Behavior empty.

Do not leave Description empty.

Do not leave steps without expected results.

Do not put credentials, real email addresses, passwords, personal names, phone numbers, or sensitive data in descriptions or preconditions.

Do not use production data.

Do not expose Qase enum numbers in the human-readable summary.

Do not update a test case without explaining the reason.

Do not create missing cases without linking them to a requirement or gap.

Do not assume unclear requirements; flag them.

Do not mark a case complete if a junior QA could not execute it from the written content alone.

Always use safe placeholder data.

Always prefer exact UI labels from the app or repository.

Always check both requirement coverage and implementation coverage.

Always include a gap analysis.

Always provide a final recommendation.

